To get the player&#39;s NAME from the table, I would use an XPath to find a list of elements and then handle that list on your own.

Here&#39;s the XPath:

`//table[@id=&#39;players_standard_pitching_clone&#39;]//td[@data-stat=&#39;player&#39;]`

This will get you a list of all players.

To use it, you need to call `findElements` so that you are getting a list.

`driver.findElements(by.XPath(&quot;//table[@id=&#39;players_standard_pitching_clone&#39;]//td[@data-stat=&#39;player&#39;]&quot;);`

Now you have a list of WebElements, whose text contain names. If you want to put the names into a list, you can do something like this:

````
List&lt;IWebElement&gt; playerNameElements = driver.findElements(by.XPath(&quot;//table[@id=&#39;players_standard_pitching_clone&#39;]//td[@data-stat=&#39;player&#39;]&quot;);
List&lt;string&gt; playerNames = new List&lt;string&gt;();

foreach (IWebElement playerElement in playerElements)
{
    playerNames.Add(playerElement.Text);
}
````

Now, `playerNames` will contain a list of strings with all of the player&#39;s names from the table.

